  "prompt": "How do I regain my bone strength after delivery?",
  "response": "To regain bone strength after delivery, consider the following strategies:\n\n1. Nutrition\n- Consume calcium-rich foods (dairy, leafy greens)\n- Take calcium and vitamin D supplements\n- Eat foods high in magnesium and phosphorus\n- Stay hydrated\n\n2. Exercise\n- Begin with gentle postpartum exercises\n- Gradually incorporate weight-bearing exercises\n- Try walking, jogging, or resistance training\n- Consult your healthcare provider before starting\n\n3. Breastfeeding considerations\n- Monitor calcium levels\n- Take recommended supplements\n- Maintain a balanced diet\n\n4. Lifestyle factors\n- Get adequate sleep\n- Manage stress\n- Limit caffeine and alcohol intake\n- Avoid smoking\n\n5. Medical guidance\n- Have a postpartum bone density check\n- Discuss concerns with your doctor\n- Consider bone health screenings\n\n6. Specific exercises\n- Yoga\n- Pilates\n- Light weightlifting\n- Walking\n- Swimming\n\n7. Hormonal balance\n- Follow up with healthcare provider\n- Monitor hormone levels\n- Consider hormone replacement if needed\n\nAlways consult your healthcare professional before starting any new exercise or supplement regimen to ensure it's appropriate for your individual health needs.",
